# ============================================================================
# CANONICAL fleet / sweep container images — THE SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH.
# ============================================================================
# Every launcher MUST `source` this file and use the variables below. NO script
# may hard-code a `ghcr.io/imazen/...` image literal — scripts/jobsys/check_canonical_images.sh
# FAILS CI if one appears. Variants (cpu / gpu / exec / version) are TAGS on
# these packages, NEVER new package names.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS: the worker image was renamed FIVE times in ~8 weeks
#   zen-jobworker -> zen-jobworker-exec -> zenfleet-worker
#     -> zenfleet-worker-exec -> zenfleet-worker-exec-gpu
# and the sweep image FOUR times (zen-metrics-sweep / -salad / -hetzner /
# zenmetrics-sweep). Each rename orphaned the "non-wasteful vastai" capability
# and the next session rebuilt it from scratch. Documentation (the CLAUDE.md
# "ONE ghcr package per artifact" rule) did not stop it because the rename
# happens at `docker build -t`, nowhere near the doc. One file to look at now.
#
# CANONICAL PACKAGES (do NOT invent a 5th — the guard rejects it):
#   zenfleet-worker   job-system worker / executor   (CPU = :latest, GPU = :gpu)
#   zenmetrics-sweep  sweep / score image
#   pycvvdp-scorer    pytorch pycvvdp scorer
#   zen-train         burn trainer
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MIGRATION IN PROGRESS: the working GPU executor still lives under the legacy
# package `zenfleet-worker-exec-gpu`. It must be re-tagged onto
# `zenfleet-worker:gpu` and the legacy package deleted, after which the line
# below changes to that and the guard's MIGRATING exception is removed. Until
# then ZEN_FLEET_IMAGE points at the legacy name so launches keep working.
# 2026-07-02: the plain :exec-gpu tag VANISHED from ghcr (later pushes created only
# variant tags) — 8 fleet boxes sat in "manifest unknown" pull loops. Default now
# points at the newest proven GPU ScoreFile executor tag. When pushing a new GPU
# exec image, ALSO re-tag it :exec-gpu (canonical tags must never be dropped).
# 2026-07-19: rebuilt with current zensim (b79315cfbf4e) + the force-surface
# observability entrypoint; pushed :exec-gpu (canonical) + this immutable pin, and
# PROVEN on a real RTX 3060 (all 6 GPU metrics JIT+ran clean — cvvdp 9.857 real JOD,
# zensim-gpu 66.277 == CPU zensim; see ~/tmp/gpu_smoke.py). Repointed off the
# 2-week-old exec-gpu-hqfillA pin (old zensim) to this proven current-zensim pin.
ZEN_FLEET_IMAGE="${ZEN_FLEET_IMAGE:-ghcr.io/imazen/zenfleet-worker:exec-gpu-zensim-b79315cfbf4e}"
ZEN_FLEET_IMAGE_CPU="${ZEN_FLEET_IMAGE_CPU:-ghcr.io/imazen/zenfleet-worker:exec}"
ZEN_SWEEP_IMAGE="${ZEN_SWEEP_IMAGE:-ghcr.io/imazen/zenmetrics-sweep:latest}"
ZEN_PYCVVDP_IMAGE="${ZEN_PYCVVDP_IMAGE:-ghcr.io/imazen/pycvvdp-scorer:0.5.4}"
